File Name: WelcomeBhavesh.java

public class WelcomeBhavesh {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String name = "Bhavesh";
        System.out.println("Hello, Welcome " + name + "!");
    }
}

#Run below commands on cmd/git bash:

Go to file location where your .java file is present (here, WelcomeBhavesh.java)

then,

javac <file name> 

here, javac WelcomeBhavesh.java --> It will create .class file on same location

Now go to Jenkins Job and add below commands in Execute Windows bash command:

cd <file location>
javac <file name>
java WelcomeBhavesh 


##Trigger Build Remotely:

Toke_Name : bhavesh2809

Use the following URL to trigger build remotely: JENKINS_URL/job/HelloWorld/build?token=TOKEN_NAME or /buildWithParameters?token=TOKEN_NAME

localhost:8080/job/HelloWorld/build?token=bhavesh2809 --> Using this URL we can run our Jenkins job remotely

